#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:26
msgid ""
"Use metrics to identify key areas where you want to extract valuable "
"insights by measuring performance and improvement. Metrics are enabled "
"when you enable retrospectives. Calibrate the type of metric you want to "
"measure, and once a run is finished you can view the output in the "
"retrospective. You can have multiple metrics configured per playbook and "
"you can edit them at any time. Metrics can be configured based on "
"numeric, time, or value input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:28
msgid ""
"These metrics can be anything that's of interest to you and your team. "
"For example, for a software release playbook you might want to have a "
"metric tracking how many bugs were detected during a run. The output of "
"the metrics you've added is provided in the retrospective. Over time, you"
" can use metrics across retrospectives to examine anomalies and refine "
"goals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:30
msgid ""
"Another example is a support incident playbook. The time to resolution "
"metric can be applied and used to identify areas that need more "
"refinement, such as tasks that might work better if they're split up so "
"goals are reached faster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:32
msgid ""
"When you delete configured metrics from a playbook, the data isn't "
"deleted, but you no longer see those metrics in the dashboard. In "
"addition, the corresponding metric field is removed from the "
"retrospective form and from published retrospectives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:35
msgid "Metrics dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:37
msgid ""
"For each run, you can enter a value per metric under the retrospective "
"section. This value can be based on whatever you are measuring, such as "
"number of bugs found per run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/repeatable-processes/metrics-and-goals.rst:39
msgid ""
"You can edit this value as many times as you'd like - for example to "
"ensure you have the correct parameters for your metric - until you've "
"published the retrospective at which point both the metrics and report "
"are no longer editable. The final value only shows up in the playbook "
"dashboard once the retrospective has been published."
msgstr ""

